; Plan 7 — better-auth has two peerOptional conflicts with our tree:
;   1. peerOptional vitest@^2||^3||^4 vs. our vitest@^1.6.1
;   2. peerOptional @tanstack/react-start (transitive vite>=7) vs. @vitejs/plugin-react@4.7's vite
;
; Neither is a real runtime dep — they're optional integrations we don't use.
; legacy-peer-deps lets npm install and npm ci both reproduce the same tree
; that was resolved locally, instead of erroring out on the peerOptional
; mismatch. Mirrors what older npm did by default.
legacy-peer-deps=true
